name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $system
desc: Returns: Telecommunications form for contact point - what communications system is required to make use of the contact.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Telecommunications form for contact point - what communications system is required to make use of the contact.

name: $value
desc: Returns: The actual contact point details, in a form that is meaningful to the designated communication system (i.e. phone number or email address).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The actual contact point details, in a form that is meaningful to the designated communication system (i.e. phone number or email address).

name: $use
desc: Returns: Identifies the purpose for the contact point.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Identifies the purpose for the contact point.

name: $rank
desc: Returns: Specifies a preferred order in which to use a set of contacts. Contacts are ranked with lower values coming before higher values.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Specifies a preferred order in which to use a set of contacts. Contacts are ranked with lower values coming before higher values.

name: $period
desc: Returns: Time period when the contact point was/is in use.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Time period when the contact point was/is in use.
